<p><strong>Default: Thinking Mode ON</strong> - Model reasons through problems step-by-step in <code>&lt;think&gt;</code> blocks.</p>
<p><strong>To disable thinking (Instruct Mode):</strong> Add this near the top of the template:</p>
<pre><code class="language-jinja"><span class="hljs-template-tag">{%- <span class="hljs-name">set</span> enable_thinking = false -%}</span>
</code></pre>
<p>In LM Studio: Dev Mode → Template → Add the line after the header comment.</p>
<p>This is a reasoning model with <code>&lt;think&gt;</code> tokens.</p>
<p>However it has an "Instruct Mode" where you can disable reasoning.</p>
<p>To disable thinking (if your tool supports it):</p>
<ul>
<li>Set <code>enable_thinking=false</code> in your inference settings</li>
<li>Or use a no-think instruct template</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: Some tools (Ollama, vLLM, Transformers) support this parameter directly.</p>
<p>Add this near the top (after line 10 or so):</p>
<p><code>{%- set enable_thinking = false -%}</code></p>
