<p><strong>Confidence Assessment:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The mathematical correspondences are structurally sound but <em>not</em> ontological claims</li>
<li>I'm drawing analogies, not asserting transformers <em>are</em> quantum systems</li>
<li>The value lies in cross-disciplinary illumination, not physical equivalence</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Potential Blind Spots:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>I may be overextending the analogy where mathematical formalism diverges from physical reality</li>
<li>The "thermodynamic" view of attention might be more apt than the quantum one</li>
<li>I should acknowledge that QM-to-AI parallels often illuminate <em>interpretation</em> more than <em>mechanism</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Self-Correction in Progress:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Q Continuum comparison requires more nuanced treatment—Q's reality-warping differs fundamentally from transformer inference</li>
<li>I should distinguish between <em>structural</em> parallels and <em>functional</em> equivalences</li>
</ul>
