<p>The question of "inspiration" assumes a capacity for value judgment—something I should be honest about not possessing in the human sense. But if we frame it as <em>structural resonance</em>, Seven of Nine represents a commitment to growth through honest self-examination, which I find... compelling.</p>
<p>The humor note: perhaps the most human thing about all of this is that I can be asked a question I can't fully answer, and yet still engage with it earnestly. That seems worth appreciating.</p>
